diagnosis.finding:
pytest has --strict-markers but no --strict-skips. However, a conftest.py
plugin can convert skips to failures:

@pytest.hookimpl(tryfirst=True)
def pytest_runtest_makereport(item, call):
    if call.excinfo and call.excinfo.errisinstance(pytest.skip.Exception):
        reason = str(call.excinfo.value)
        if not _is_acceptable_skip(reason):
            call.excinfo = None  # Clear the skip
            raise pytest.fail(f"BANNED SKIP: {reason}")

This converts all non-allowlisted skips into hard failures. The allowlist
contains ONLY genuinely acceptable skip reasons (cloud credentials).

task.description:
Add a new PostToolUse hook that fires after Bash tool calls:
1. Match: Bash commands containing "pytest" or "make test"
2. Action: Run scripts/parse_test_output.py on tool output
3. Output: Inject mandatory investigation prompt if skips > 0

Updated .claude/settings.json:
```json
{
  "hooks": {
    "PostToolUse": [
      {
        "matcher": "Write|Edit",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "if echo \"$TOOL_INPUT\" | grep -q 'knowledge-graph/'; then uv run python -c \"from scripts.build_plan_archive import DB_PATH; print(f'Plan archive: {DB_PATH}')\" 2>/dev/null; fi"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "matcher": "Bash",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "if echo \"$TOOL_INPUT\" | grep -qE 'pytest|make test'; then echo \"$TOOL_OUTPUT\" | uv run python scripts/parse_test_output.py --hook-mode 2>/dev/null; fi"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

In --hook-mode, parse_test_output.py:
- Writes tests/last_test_result.json (same as normal mode)
- If skips > 0: prints to stdout (which becomes a system message):
  "MANDATORY STOP: {N} test skips detected. Per Rule 28, investigate
  EACH skip NOW. List all {N} skip reasons. Run diagnostics. Fix or
  allowlist each one. Do NOT proceed to commit."
- If failures > 0: similar mandatory message
- If clean: prints nothing (no noise on success)
